Prime Minister Kassim Majaliwa has congratulated Simba SC for securing their 1-0 win in the African Champions League match against AS Vital in Kinshasa, DRC on Friday night. Winding up the Bunge meeting in Dodoma on Saturday, the Premier praised Simba and Namungo FC for progressing into CAF Champions League and Confederation Cup group stages respectively. He appreciated Msimbazi side Chief Executive Officer Babra Gonzalez for coming up with a creative idea that aims at promoting the country's tourism sector. Recently Simba SC unveiled special kits for CAF Champions League with a message “Visit Tanzania” as a strategy of promoting the country’s tourism sector.